WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:17.330 --> 00:00:20.540
Did you know there's an awesome treasure at the end of this sea?!

3
00:00:20.540 --> 00:00:23.340
And whoever gets it becomes King of the Pirates!

4
00:00:23.340 --> 00:00:24.960
Isn't that exciting?!

5
00:00:24.960 --> 00:00:28.010
Cool new adventures are waiting out there!

6
00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:38.060
BON VOYAGE! Light the ember of courage and let the fire grow

7
00:00:38.060 --> 00:00:45.660
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

8
00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:48.210
Back when we first started

9
00:00:48.210 --> 00:00:53.430
we had separate ideas about where we would soon go

10
00:00:53.740 --> 00:00:55.380
Things have changed now,

11
00:00:55.380 --> 00:01:00.440
when we look towards our dreams we all share one telescope

12
00:01:00.730 --> 00:01:05.680
When you find that your heart's been led astray

13
00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:09.980
time to calibrate your compasses

14
00:01:09.980 --> 00:01:13.010
Set a new course, turn the tables now

15
00:01:13.010 --> 00:01:20.300
BON VOYAGE! Shed your previous baggage, forget the past

16
00:01:20.300 --> 00:01:27.140
Smiles can weather a storm, we know that better than anyone

17
00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:29.080
Don't you fret,

18
00:01:29.080 --> 00:01:34.900
tears shed along the way to your dreams are not in vain

19
00:01:34.900 --> 00:01:41.100
You know that you're all PRECIOUS IN MY LIFE

20
00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:49.210
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

21
00:01:55.600 --> 00:02:00.270
<b>Deathpiea</b>

22
00:02:07.190 --> 00:02:10.360
Rubber doesn't conduct lightning!

23
00:02:10.940 --> 00:02:14.740
Against a rubber man,
Enel's attacks are useless!

24
00:02:16.410 --> 00:02:17.700
Enel...

25
00:02:18.790 --> 00:02:19.740
can be defeated!

26
00:02:33.340 --> 00:02:37.800
Just what the hell are you?!

27
00:02:39.470 --> 00:02:40.850
I'm Luffy.

28
00:02:41.600 --> 00:02:43.980
I'm a pirate and a rubber man.

29
00:02:45.440 --> 00:02:46.440
Rubber?

30
00:02:46.900 --> 00:02:48.440
Of course...!

31
00:02:48.440 --> 00:02:51.820
Rubber doesn't exist
in the White-White Sea.

32
00:02:51.820 --> 00:02:54.780
Lightning doesn't work on me!

33
00:02:54.780 --> 00:02:55.740
Mantra.

34
00:03:02.410 --> 00:03:03.710
Gum-Gum...

35
00:03:04.160 --> 00:03:06.370
Whip!

36
00:03:10.750 --> 00:03:13.210
Spear!

37
00:03:26.270 --> 00:03:27.190
Luffy!

38
00:03:33.070 --> 00:03:34.610
Don't get cocky.

39
00:03:36.400 --> 00:03:39.910
Lightning can do more
than electrocute.

40
00:03:40.660 --> 00:03:45.910
If it's ineffective, I'll adjust
my fighting style accordingly.

41
00:03:47.620 --> 00:03:50.330
Hitting me won't work either!

42
00:03:53.670 --> 00:03:55.170
Dammit!

43
00:03:55.800 --> 00:03:59.050
So this guy can predict
my moves, too!?

44
00:03:59.890 --> 00:04:02.890
Just what is this "rubber"?

45
00:04:02.890 --> 00:04:06.350
No, hold on a second...
He's merely a paramecia.

46
00:04:06.890 --> 00:04:10.230
He should retain his physical form
for the most part.

47
00:04:10.770 --> 00:04:12.520
Lightning...

48
00:04:12.520 --> 00:04:13.980
Forge!

49
00:04:17.820 --> 00:04:21.740
I don't have time to play
with the likes of you.

50
00:04:21.740 --> 00:04:25.950
He's reforming the pole...
into a blade?!

51
00:04:30.420 --> 00:04:32.540
Think of it as lightning given form!

52
00:04:38.590 --> 00:04:41.050
Just as I thought,
you're weak to slashing.

53
00:04:41.050 --> 00:04:41.930
Yup.

54
00:04:43.760 --> 00:04:45.390
Don't admit it!

55
00:04:46.140 --> 00:04:48.180
Gum-Gum...

56
00:04:48.180 --> 00:04:49.140
Gatlin–

57
00:04:51.020 --> 00:04:52.230
He's gone!

58
00:04:52.860 --> 00:04:54.650
Luffy! Behind you!

59
00:04:59.110 --> 00:05:01.740
He's moving through the gold!

60
00:05:24.550 --> 00:05:26.010
Ow, it's hot!

61
00:05:28.020 --> 00:05:31.770
Lightning doesn't work, but the heat
from this trident does just fine, huh?!

62
00:05:32.730 --> 00:05:34.310
Gum-Gum...

63
00:05:36.650 --> 00:05:39.110
Battle-Axe!

64
00:05:49.200 --> 00:05:51.080
You impudent brat!

65
00:05:51.620 --> 00:05:53.540
Gum-Gum...

66
00:05:53.540 --> 00:05:56.750
Gatling!

67
00:06:06.850 --> 00:06:09.310
It's not like you grew more arms!

68
00:06:13.480 --> 00:06:14.520
Luffy!

69
00:06:15.520 --> 00:06:17.650
Sightseeing on a sky island...

70
00:06:17.650 --> 00:06:21.490
What terrible timing, Blue Sea man.

71
00:06:23.030 --> 00:06:27.450
Remember, I am God;
I do as I please.

72
00:06:28.450 --> 00:06:31.750
I will reshape this world as I see fit!

73
00:06:32.160 --> 00:06:36.790
Some Blue Sea brat wanders up here
and thinks he can ruin my plans?

74
00:06:36.790 --> 00:06:39.840
What a farce!

75
00:06:41.800 --> 00:06:48.390
Now, shall we witness the collapse
of this nation together?

76
00:06:52.930 --> 00:06:53.940
Don't tell me...

77
00:06:54.440 --> 00:06:59.190
Max 200 Million Volts: Vari!

78
00:07:14.500 --> 00:07:15.870
Horsey-Bird!

79
00:07:15.870 --> 00:07:18.460
The ship's moving!
What're we gonna do?!

80
00:07:23.550 --> 00:07:27.760
Luffy! Nami!

81
00:07:31.010 --> 00:07:33.720
Behold! It rises!

82
00:07:33.720 --> 00:07:40.060
The ark that will deliver me to that
fabled land, the Endless Vearth...

83
00:07:40.820 --> 00:07:42.150
Maxim!

84
00:07:50.320 --> 00:07:51.740
I-It's rising!

85
00:07:56.790 --> 00:08:00.290
Crap, crap, crap, crap, crap...

86
00:08:00.290 --> 00:08:01.250
We have to escape!

87
00:08:02.130 --> 00:08:05.210
Luffy! Hurry up and beat Enel!

88
00:08:05.210 --> 00:08:07.800
Ahh! W-W-Wait a second!

89
00:08:07.800 --> 00:08:10.550
If we defeat Enel,
isn't the ship going to fall?

90
00:08:10.550 --> 00:08:13.220
Ahh, but if we don't,
the sky island will be destroyed.

91
00:08:13.220 --> 00:08:16.350
And if we stay here...

92
00:08:16.980 --> 00:08:18.640
we'll be taken away somewhere!

93
00:08:22.020 --> 00:08:25.480
What're we gonna do, Luffy?!

94
00:08:34.950 --> 00:08:37.160
Stop panicking so much.

95
00:08:37.710 --> 00:08:40.040
But... I mean...!

96
00:08:40.830 --> 00:08:43.590
You're on the crew of
the future King of the Pirates.

97
00:08:45.170 --> 00:08:47.970
Stop looking so pathetic.

98
00:08:53.510 --> 00:08:55.600
King of the Pirates?

99
00:08:55.600 --> 00:08:58.980
And where is his kingdom?

100
00:09:03.150 --> 00:09:06.360
He stands above all...
as the great king of the seas!

101
00:09:10.320 --> 00:09:12.070
Most impressive.

102
00:09:12.070 --> 00:09:15.030
Then let's settle this
right here in the sky!

103
00:09:42.190 --> 00:09:43.690
Look, Horsey-Bird!

104
00:09:43.690 --> 00:09:45.610
It stopped!

105
00:09:46.480 --> 00:09:50.030
It's stuck in the vearth
and can't go any higher!

106
00:09:50.400 --> 00:09:53.280
But it's only a matter of time!
It's grinding out a path!

107
00:09:55.410 --> 00:09:56.910
No, let's stay back!

108
00:09:56.910 --> 00:09:59.040
We'll get in his way if we go!

109
00:09:59.040 --> 00:10:01.000
Luffy is a warrior from the Blue Sea!

110
00:10:01.330 --> 00:10:05.080
We shouldn't interfere
in a warriors' duel!

111
00:10:08.630 --> 00:10:14.390
The circuit for this ark's ultimate purpose
is already up and running.

112
00:10:14.390 --> 00:10:20.310
It's called Deathpiea—despair incarnate
and the salvation of this world!

113
00:10:23.810 --> 00:10:25.690
What's he going to do?!

114
00:10:44.080 --> 00:10:46.250
Wh-What is that?!

115
00:10:49.130 --> 00:10:50.960
Chief!

116
00:10:51.510 --> 00:10:53.880
Something's wrong with
the sky above Upper Yard!

117
00:10:53.880 --> 00:10:55.430
The sky?

118
00:10:55.430 --> 00:10:58.680
Yeah, it got dark all of a sudden.

119
00:10:58.680 --> 00:11:02.600
This is the first time I've seen
Skypiea's sky like that!

120
00:11:02.600 --> 00:11:04.600
It's creepy.

121
00:11:04.600 --> 00:11:07.560
Has something befallen the warriors?

122
00:11:09.190 --> 00:11:14.610
To see such thick clouds in
the sky of the White-White Sea...

123
00:11:15.990 --> 00:11:18.780
That's right! They're thunderclouds.

124
00:11:18.780 --> 00:11:24.080
Using my energy, Deathpiea
discharges thunderclouds

125
00:11:24.080 --> 00:11:26.670
with extremely turbulent currents.

126
00:11:26.670 --> 00:11:27.670
Thunderclouds?!

127
00:11:28.290 --> 00:11:32.630
Soon, the clouds will
accumulate enough energy

128
00:11:32.630 --> 00:11:35.800
to shroud all of Skypiea in darkness.

129
00:11:36.550 --> 00:11:40.890
On my command, dozens
of lightning bolts will rain down,

130
00:11:40.890 --> 00:11:44.020
annihilating the entire country!

131
00:11:45.730 --> 00:11:48.020
Allow me to demonstrate.

132
00:11:59.490 --> 00:12:01.450
It's coming from Upper Yard!

133
00:12:02.240 --> 00:12:03.540
Hurry to the ships!

134
00:12:04.040 --> 00:12:08.420
Keep calm and don't panic!
Head to Cloud End!

135
00:12:13.050 --> 00:12:15.050
How dare you, Enel?!

136
00:12:23.140 --> 00:12:24.140
Enel...!

137
00:12:33.440 --> 00:12:35.610
What did you just...?

138
00:12:35.610 --> 00:12:40.160
I teased the angels a little.

139
00:12:40.160 --> 00:12:43.740
You think it's okay for a god
to get rid of everything?!

140
00:12:43.740 --> 00:12:44.830
That's right.

141
00:12:44.830 --> 00:12:47.580
Life, land, anything I please.

142
00:12:47.580 --> 00:12:51.290
And that includes you!

143
00:12:51.290 --> 00:12:53.920
The preparations for the party
have already begun!

144
00:13:00.130 --> 00:13:02.760
O-Ouch! Ow, ow, ow, ow...

145
00:13:05.510 --> 00:13:07.140
This is a high-voltage spear!

146
00:13:15.570 --> 00:13:17.360
Hot!

147
00:13:26.330 --> 00:13:27.950
Dammit!

148
00:13:27.950 --> 00:13:32.460
Isn't there some way I can counter
that predicting movements thing?!

149
00:13:34.500 --> 00:13:35.540
I've got it!

150
00:13:36.630 --> 00:13:40.010
Gum-Gum...

151
00:13:40.010 --> 00:13:40.970
Daze...

152
00:13:41.840 --> 00:13:44.220
What the hell are you doing, Luffy?!

153
00:13:55.560 --> 00:13:59.530
He's dodging the attacks
on pure instinct!

154
00:13:59.530 --> 00:14:04.490
No, he's like grass,
just swaying with the wind.

155
00:14:04.820 --> 00:14:08.200
His mind is empty,
so Enel can't read it!

156
00:14:14.080 --> 00:14:16.290
When I'm in a daze...

157
00:14:18.340 --> 00:14:20.460
I can't attack him either!

158
00:14:20.460 --> 00:14:21.300
You moron!

159
00:14:21.670 --> 00:14:25.930
If I could somehow catch him,
I could even the odds.

160
00:14:26.600 --> 00:14:27.760
I've got it!

161
00:14:31.640 --> 00:14:35.350
Gum-Gum Octopus!

162
00:14:35.350 --> 00:14:37.230
Enough!

163
00:14:37.230 --> 00:14:39.690
No more weird ideas!

164
00:14:39.690 --> 00:14:43.200
It seems mantra is not to your liking.

165
00:14:43.200 --> 00:14:44.700
That's to be expected!

166
00:14:44.700 --> 00:14:48.330
After all, it is yet another
mark of my supremacy!

167
00:14:49.160 --> 00:14:50.540
Over there should work!

168
00:14:52.080 --> 00:14:54.460
Gum-Gum...

169
00:14:54.460 --> 00:14:56.290
No matter what you do,

170
00:14:56.290 --> 00:14:59.840
you're just a fool who happens
to be immune to lightning!

171
00:14:59.840 --> 00:15:01.880
...Octopus...

172
00:15:02.210 --> 00:15:04.050
What? He's going for the ship?!

173
00:15:04.050 --> 00:15:06.930
...Fireworks!

174
00:15:10.930 --> 00:15:12.060
Imbecile!

175
00:15:12.060 --> 00:15:13.640
You can't hit me!

176
00:15:13.640 --> 00:15:16.440
Are you trying to destroy
the ship?! How futile!

177
00:15:42.840 --> 00:15:43.960
Of course!

178
00:15:43.960 --> 00:15:45.470
They're ricocheting!

179
00:15:45.470 --> 00:15:48.760
Luffy isn't controlling the punches
that rebound from the wall!

180
00:15:49.260 --> 00:15:51.430
I won't let you get away anymore!

181
00:15:51.430 --> 00:15:54.060
Gum-Gum...

182
00:15:55.230 --> 00:15:56.190
W-Wait!

183
00:15:56.190 --> 00:15:58.940
...Bazooka!

184
00:16:15.160 --> 00:16:16.160
No...!

185
00:16:16.160 --> 00:16:17.330
He's coming!

186
00:16:19.290 --> 00:16:21.460
I... I have to escape!

187
00:16:21.460 --> 00:16:25.010
Gum-Gum...

188
00:16:25.460 --> 00:16:26.840
Here it comes!

189
00:16:28.880 --> 00:16:32.220
I... I have to evade it!

190
00:16:32.220 --> 00:16:35.600
...Rifle!

191
00:17:05.050 --> 00:17:07.340
The ship is leaving the vearth!

192
00:17:09.510 --> 00:17:11.180
Oh no! What should we do?

193
00:17:11.180 --> 00:17:13.430
The ship's about to fly away!

194
00:17:15.560 --> 00:17:16.270
You did it...

195
00:17:16.640 --> 00:17:17.600
You did it!

196
00:17:18.100 --> 00:17:20.060
B-But the ship...

197
00:17:20.440 --> 00:17:21.310
It's flying away!

198
00:17:23.650 --> 00:17:24.940
No way...

199
00:17:25.440 --> 00:17:26.780
Even after all that?

200
00:17:27.190 --> 00:17:31.240
You fools! I-Is that all you've got?

201
00:17:36.200 --> 00:17:41.080
Once I am rid of you,
the world will be mine!

202
00:17:45.040 --> 00:17:50.630
I will be feared, worshipped,
and revered by all once more.

203
00:17:51.090 --> 00:17:52.880
That is my world!

204
00:17:53.930 --> 00:17:57.390
Vermin like you are no match for me!

205
00:17:59.350 --> 00:18:03.900
For me... nothing is impossible!

206
00:18:08.190 --> 00:18:11.240
I am the almighty God!

207
00:18:12.820 --> 00:18:13.780
Run!

208
00:18:16.580 --> 00:18:20.160
Look! Something is floating
in the sky above Upper Yard!

209
00:18:20.750 --> 00:18:22.160
A... A ship?!

210
00:18:22.500 --> 00:18:26.790
That can't be! A flying ship...
I've never heard of such a thing!

211
00:18:33.130 --> 00:18:36.350
Is that ship what's
making the sky go dark?!

212
00:18:36.350 --> 00:18:38.850
God must be on that ship!

213
00:18:41.310 --> 00:18:41.980
Hey!

214
00:18:42.850 --> 00:18:43.770
Hurry! Run!

215
00:18:44.690 --> 00:18:46.940
Board the ships!

216
00:18:51.360 --> 00:18:54.530
Lots of ships are leaving Angel Island!

217
00:18:57.410 --> 00:19:01.870
What's going on? Where did
those dark clouds come from?

218
00:19:01.870 --> 00:19:04.000
Hm? Someone is coming this way!

219
00:19:05.000 --> 00:19:07.710
Ahoy, Shandians!

220
00:19:08.090 --> 00:19:10.960
You should prepare
your ships immediately too!

221
00:19:10.960 --> 00:19:13.920
There's no hope for
this country anymore!

222
00:19:13.920 --> 00:19:14.510
What?

223
00:19:15.010 --> 00:19:16.390
Escape!

224
00:19:16.390 --> 00:19:17.340
To the Blue Sea!

225
00:19:17.340 --> 00:19:20.010
T-To the Blue Sea?!

226
00:19:27.400 --> 00:19:28.190
A ship...

227
00:19:29.770 --> 00:19:32.110
God... Enel...

228
00:19:35.990 --> 00:19:38.620
Bear witness, rubber man...

229
00:19:39.620 --> 00:19:42.410
to the despair of a falling island.

230
00:19:47.580 --> 00:19:48.960
The sky island is no more.

231
00:19:49.500 --> 00:19:52.250
The angels' lives will be extinguished.

232
00:19:52.750 --> 00:19:54.920
No one can stop it now...

233
00:19:56.680 --> 00:19:58.180
not even you!

234
00:19:59.050 --> 00:19:59.590
Stop it!

235
00:20:00.010 --> 00:20:01.720
Lightning...

236
00:20:02.060 --> 00:20:03.010
The golden wall...!

237
00:20:03.010 --> 00:20:04.350
Why you...!

238
00:20:05.140 --> 00:20:06.730
...Forge!

239
00:20:06.730 --> 00:20:07.600
H-Hot!

240
00:20:08.850 --> 00:20:10.560
He melted it with electricity!

241
00:20:10.560 --> 00:20:13.530
Dammit, it burns!

242
00:20:15.610 --> 00:20:16.780
Luffy!

243
00:20:18.280 --> 00:20:21.320
It won't come off! Dammit!

244
00:20:21.700 --> 00:20:23.830
Blue Sea rubber man...

245
00:20:23.830 --> 00:20:28.540
Why should I even sully
my hands fighting you?

246
00:20:28.540 --> 00:20:31.500
Take this off, you bastard!

247
00:20:31.500 --> 00:20:35.960
After all, I can't bear
taking another hit from you.

248
00:20:37.880 --> 00:20:39.800
So, why don't we...

249
00:20:40.300 --> 00:20:43.010
part ways right here and now?

250
00:20:43.010 --> 00:20:46.220
In honor of your valiant efforts,
I bestow upon you...

251
00:20:47.770 --> 00:20:49.690
this gold!

252
00:21:09.710 --> 00:21:10.710
Luffy!

253
00:21:11.580 --> 00:21:16.630
With you out of the picture,
the world will be mine once more.

254
00:21:18.720 --> 00:21:23.050
There will be no one
in the world who can defeat me.

255
00:21:24.680 --> 00:21:26.390
"In the world"?!

256
00:21:28.730 --> 00:21:30.350
Are you stupid or what?

257
00:21:30.350 --> 00:21:32.480
Plenty of people can!

258
00:21:33.100 --> 00:21:37.860
Back where we're from, there are
monsters everywhere!

259
00:21:38.610 --> 00:21:39.950
Compared to them...

260
00:21:42.410 --> 00:21:44.530
You're a noisy brat, aren't you?

261
00:21:45.660 --> 00:21:47.120
Fall!

262
00:21:47.490 --> 00:21:49.200
Together with the sky island!

263
00:21:50.160 --> 00:21:52.500
You're just a...!

264
00:21:52.500 --> 00:21:53.880
N-No!

265
00:21:55.500 --> 00:21:57.210
Luffy!

266
00:22:04.260 --> 00:22:05.180
Luffy...

267
00:22:05.720 --> 00:22:08.540
Damn you!

268
00:22:09.470 --> 00:22:11.690
That's Luffy, Horsey-Bird!

269
00:22:12.020 --> 00:22:13.850
Luffy's falling!

270
00:22:16.480 --> 00:22:19.570
That's... Aisa and Pierre!

271
00:22:19.570 --> 00:22:21.530
So that's who it was...

272
00:22:21.530 --> 00:22:25.410
that sneaky whisper I've been hearing.

273
00:22:26.030 --> 00:22:31.540
Fight me!

274
00:22:31.540 --> 00:22:33.620
Luffy! We're coming to save you!

275
00:22:35.290 --> 00:22:36.670
How annoying!

276
00:22:36.670 --> 00:22:39.050
Just accept your fate!

277
00:22:39.050 --> 00:22:41.670
Aisa! Pierre! Watch out! Dodge it!

278
00:22:42.130 --> 00:22:45.640
Enel!

279
00:22:46.640 --> 00:22:48.470
God's Reckoning:

280
00:22:50.060 --> 00:22:51.850
El Thor!

281
00:23:04.240 --> 00:23:06.240
Luffy!

282
00:23:07.490 --> 00:23:11.620
Aisa! Pierre!

283
00:23:13.870 --> 00:23:15.210
That took a toll, even for me.

284
00:23:15.830 --> 00:23:18.880
However... this is the conclusion.

285
00:23:29.470 --> 00:23:31.430
What a large ship...

286
00:23:32.430 --> 00:23:35.890
So that's the ark that
the Holy Host was forced to build.

287
00:23:40.980 --> 00:23:43.320
Here, the northeast of the island.

288
00:23:43.320 --> 00:23:47.660
After they get the gold,
we're meeting up at this shore.

289
00:23:48.110 --> 00:23:51.620
So once everyone's there,
you'll be leaving?

290
00:23:51.620 --> 00:23:55.910
I'd settle for just the treasure,
if I'm being totally honest!

291
00:23:57.040 --> 00:23:59.290
– N... Nami...
– N... Nami...

292
00:23:59.920 --> 00:24:04.260
They're heading back to their
ship... at the northeast shore.

293
00:24:04.260 --> 00:24:07.510
I'll go there... and wait
for everyone to arrive.

294
00:24:07.510 --> 00:24:10.180
I must help them
get back to the Blue Sea!

295
00:24:10.760 --> 00:24:14.600
I'm the only one who can show them
how to get off this sky island!

296
00:24:17.480 --> 00:24:19.940
I have to hurry to the Going Merry!

297
00:24:22.820 --> 00:24:23.820
Oh, Nami dear...

298
00:24:23.820 --> 00:24:26.610
Hmm... What is it?

299
00:24:28.660 --> 00:24:29.410
No!

300
00:24:30.870 --> 00:24:34.160
I want to stay in the dream
with my sweet Nami.

301
00:24:34.160 --> 00:24:35.580
Hm...? Nami?

302
00:24:36.250 --> 00:24:37.210
Nami!

303
00:24:41.290 --> 00:24:44.380
Wh-What the hell is that?!

304
00:24:45.510 --> 00:24:47.590
Mellorine... Mellorine, Mellorine...

305
00:24:47.590 --> 00:24:50.970
Mellorine, Mellorine,
Mellorine, Mellorine, Mello–

306
00:24:50.970 --> 00:24:52.510
Nami!

307
00:24:53.140 --> 00:24:54.810
What in the world...?

308
00:24:58.140 --> 00:25:00.020
Hey! Wake up, idiot!

309
00:25:00.020 --> 00:25:02.980
This is no time to be in bed!

310
00:25:04.270 --> 00:25:06.150
What was...

311
00:25:06.150 --> 00:25:07.490
Hm? I was...!

312
00:25:07.820 --> 00:25:09.450
Shut up and get ready!

313
00:25:09.450 --> 00:25:12.030
Huh? Get ready?

314
00:25:12.570 --> 00:25:14.160
We're gonna rescue Nami!

315
00:25:14.830 --> 00:25:16.540
Rescue?

316
00:25:16.540 --> 00:25:17.950
Res–

317
00:25:18.660 --> 00:25:22.380
That's right! Now I remember!
God! God appeared!

318
00:25:36.180 --> 00:25:37.140
Oh no...

319
00:25:37.720 --> 00:25:40.140
God, God, God, God...

320
00:25:38.060 --> 00:25:40.520
He isn't here anymore!
He's long gone!

321
00:25:40.140 --> 00:25:45.320
Tremble, tremble, tremble,
fumble, fumble, fumble...

322
00:25:42.060 --> 00:25:45.320
He's the one who kidnapped Nami!

323
00:25:45.320 --> 00:25:46.820
K-Kidnapped?!

324
00:25:47.190 --> 00:25:51.070
Dammit! It's our fault she was taken!

325
00:25:51.820 --> 00:25:53.780
It's because she's so cute!

326
00:25:53.780 --> 00:25:55.910
Kidnapped, huh...?

327
00:25:57.200 --> 00:25:58.750
Where did he take her?

328
00:26:01.920 --> 00:26:02.830
Up there!

329
00:26:04.130 --> 00:26:05.500
What?!

330
00:26:06.290 --> 00:26:09.960
What is that?! A ship...?!
In the forest?!

331
00:26:10.340 --> 00:26:12.630
It was brief, but I caught
a glimpse of her.

332
00:26:13.680 --> 00:26:15.970
Nami is on that ship.

333
00:26:15.970 --> 00:26:19.600
It doesn't matter what that thing is!

334
00:26:20.100 --> 00:26:22.230
What matters is that her T-shirt's off.

335
00:26:22.230 --> 00:26:24.560
That definitely doesn't matter!

336
00:26:25.560 --> 00:26:28.360
I don't understand this at all.

337
00:26:28.360 --> 00:26:30.240
Where's Conis? Or the weird knight?

338
00:26:31.280 --> 00:26:34.360
I don't get it either,
but we have to hurry!

339
00:26:43.870 --> 00:26:45.880
Hey, where are we going, Sanji?!

340
00:26:45.880 --> 00:26:48.090
Where else?! That ship!

341
00:26:48.090 --> 00:26:49.590
Wh-Wh-What?!

342
00:26:49.590 --> 00:26:52.220
If we wait any longer,
we won't be able to board!

343
00:26:52.920 --> 00:26:53.800
It's now or never!

344
00:26:53.800 --> 00:26:57.600
Um, and I wouldn't happen
to be going too, would I?

345
00:26:57.600 --> 00:26:58.680
Of course you are!

346
00:26:58.680 --> 00:27:01.720
You've got that thing,
right?! The belly rope?

347
00:27:01.720 --> 00:27:03.850
Oh, you mean "Usopp Aah-eeh-ah"?!

348
00:27:03.850 --> 00:27:06.230
I'll let you borrow it,
and I can just stay h–

349
00:27:06.230 --> 00:27:07.480
Just hurry up!

350
00:27:07.480 --> 00:27:08.900
I don't want to! W-Wait a sec!

351
00:27:08.900 --> 00:27:12.320
Idiot! There's no time to waste!

352
00:27:12.320 --> 00:27:18.870
I'm coming for you,
my sweet Nami!

353
00:27:22.620 --> 00:27:25.500
Now that the Ark Maxim
has been activated,

354
00:27:25.500 --> 00:27:29.710
no amount of crying or screaming
can save this country.

355
00:27:30.920 --> 00:27:34.670
What's wrong? Be grateful
you survived this long.

356
00:27:34.670 --> 00:27:36.840
Spare no thought for the weak.

357
00:27:37.390 --> 00:27:40.810
There must be a future
you desire, yes?

358
00:27:41.180 --> 00:27:42.560
A future I desire...

359
00:27:43.470 --> 00:27:44.730
Yes, there is one.

360
00:27:46.350 --> 00:27:51.360
But if I go along with you,
it'll be no different than being alone.

361
00:27:53.530 --> 00:27:57.530
Let's get this party started!
It's the gold-hunting eve festival!

362
00:27:57.530 --> 00:27:59.990
Let's get the treasure!

363
00:27:59.990 --> 00:28:02.620
– Gold!
– Gold!

364
00:28:06.960 --> 00:28:12.090
Where's the fun in getting
what you want all by yourself?

365
00:28:12.550 --> 00:28:18.010
Honestly, there are lots of things
I want and so much I'd love to do...

366
00:28:18.010 --> 00:28:21.760
but if I have to abandon my crew
and go with you instead...

367
00:28:24.470 --> 00:28:27.940
then I don't want anything anymore!

368
00:28:28.940 --> 00:28:31.900
You don't want anything?

369
00:28:39.070 --> 00:28:41.660
That includes your life, right?

370
00:28:44.790 --> 00:28:46.000
What's going on?!

371
00:28:46.000 --> 00:28:47.210
Hey, Suu?

372
00:28:51.290 --> 00:28:55.380
Neither Usopp nor Sanji
were in any shape to move around!

373
00:28:55.840 --> 00:28:57.090
What happened?!

374
00:28:59.340 --> 00:29:00.800
Why aren't they here?

375
00:29:01.340 --> 00:29:02.850
Where have they gone?

376
00:29:03.300 --> 00:29:04.470
<b>Um...</b>

377
00:29:04.470 --> 00:29:05.600
<b>Oh, right!</b>

378
00:29:05.600 --> 00:29:08.310
<b>The guy with the cool eyebrows</b>
<b>woke up first...</b>

379
00:29:06.390 --> 00:29:08.640
Sanji woke up...

380
00:29:08.640 --> 00:29:11.350
and made Usopp get up too.

381
00:29:08.850 --> 00:29:10.810
<b>and he woke up the liar</b>
<b>and he woke up the liar
with the long nose.</b>

382
00:29:10.810 --> 00:29:12.860
<b>They ran as fast as they could...</b>

383
00:29:11.350 --> 00:29:13.610
Then they both ran...

384
00:29:13.110 --> 00:29:14.110
<b>used a weird gadget...</b>

385
00:29:13.610 --> 00:29:15.570
and jumped... straight up?

386
00:29:14.110 --> 00:29:15.570
<b>and went to that flying ship.</b>

387
00:29:16.190 --> 00:29:19.240
What?! You don't mean...!
They went to that ship?!

388
00:29:22.120 --> 00:29:24.990
Their bodies still haven't...

389
00:29:25.620 --> 00:29:28.500
How reckless!

390
00:29:48.560 --> 00:29:55.020
Usopp Aah-eeh-ah-eeh...
hold on! Ah-eeh...

391
00:29:55.770 --> 00:30:00.490
God or not, if he lays
a single finger on Nami...

392
00:30:01.150 --> 00:30:04.070
I will become the Blue Sea devil!

393
00:30:06.910 --> 00:30:10.000
Nami!

394
00:30:17.210 --> 00:30:18.630
Luffy...

395
00:30:18.630 --> 00:30:20.920
I'm gonna borrow your resolve!

396
00:30:25.070 --> 00:30:30.590
When you're lost and alone, call out and lead me to your side

397
00:30:30.810 --> 00:30:36.010
As you wander far from home, you search the sky and never hide

398
00:30:36.010 --> 00:30:38.810
You are so much like the moon

399
00:30:38.810 --> 00:30:43.460
Calmer than a star, your twinkling's lost

400
00:30:46.910 --> 00:30:55.860
A deep reflection shines, you slowly leave, fading, and what's the cost?

401
00:30:55.920 --> 00:31:01.090
Stay as you are, don't lose your way

402
00:31:01.090 --> 00:31:09.400
Let my words guide you, and look ahead until the day!

403
00:31:10.040 --> 00:31:16.290
Don't give up on your dreams, through endless nights they come to you

404
00:31:16.290 --> 00:31:21.910
If you stop, you'll never see them shining through!

405
00:31:23.150 --> 00:31:27.680
Will you return? Maybe not... Will you learn? I hope you do

406
00:31:27.680 --> 00:31:34.070
Please put your past to rest, and live your life anew.
